{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
On August 10, 1979, Yachting Partners sent petitioner a letter advising him that the Colinga\rquote s records for the 1978-79 season would not be of \u8220\'3fgreat assistance\u8221\'3f to him in estimating operating expenses because they showed an unrealistically low picture. According to the letter, the original purchase survey, slipping, and work expenses were not included in the 1978-79 records. Furthermore, all other expenses, such as the replacement of the radar, winter slipping, and various repairs, were carried forward to the following season. Thus, the 1978-79 records only showed income and a few of the day-to-day expenses.
\par 
}
}
