It is fundamental that a corporation is a separate entity from its inception. We have said that \u8220\'3fa corporate \u8216\'3fstraw\u8217\'3f may be used to separate apparent from actual ownership of property, without incurring the tax consequences of an actual transfer; but to prevent evasion or abuse of the two-tiered tax structure, a taxpayer\rquote s claim that his controlled corporation should be disregarded will be closely scrutinized. If the corporation was intended to, or did in fact, act in its own name with respect to property, its ownership thereof will not be disregarded.\u8221\'3f 
